#####################################################
#FOR ASSIGN INTERFACES and SOURCES to FIREWALL ZONES#
#####################################################

# INVENTORY_HOST = all/list of inventory hosts separated by ",".
    # If "all" -> the configuration will be applied to all inventory hosts.
    # It is forbidden to include the same interface in several firewall zones.
    # If you want to apply the settings to a group of hosts or to all hosts, then make sure that each host has the interfaces specified in the #INTERFACE_LIST parameter.
    # Configurations like "all" have low priority over host groups (separated by ",") or individual hosts.
###
# FIREWALL_ZONE_NAME_TMPLT = name of the firewall zone template configured in the files "01_conf_custom_firewall_zones_templates" and "01_conf_standard_firewall_zones_templates".
###
# INTERFACE_LIST = list of interfaces, separated by ",".
    # If interface names are not used, then set "empty".
###
# SOURCE_LIST = list of sources/ipset, separated by ",".
    # ipset must be preconfigured in file "02_conf_ipsets".
    # Higher priority than setting "INTERFACE_LIST".
###
# FORWARD_PORTS_SET = name of forward ports set for apply to firewall zone. To configure #FORWARD_PORTS_SET edit file "03_conf_zone_forward_ports_sets".
    # DST-NAT configuration.
    # With port forwarding, all traffic sent to a particular port will be redirected either to another port on the local system or to a port on the external system.
    # If forwarding to an external network is required, you must also configure masquerading (SRC-NAT).
    # Possible values: 
	# some_forward_ports_set_name (for apply some forward ports rules to firewall zone)
	# empty (for don't apply any forward ports rules to firewall zone).
###
# RICH_RULES_SET = name of rich rules set for apply to firewall zone. To configure #RICH_RULES_SET edit file "04_conf_zone_rich_rules_sets".
    # Possible values: 
	# some_rich_rules_set_name (for apply some rich rules to firewall zone)
	# empty (for don't apply any rich rules to firewall zone).
###
#INVENTORY_HOST		#FIREWALL_ZONE_NAME_TMPLT	#INTERFACE_LIST	  #SOURCE_LIST				#FORWARD_PORTS_SET	#RICH_RULES_SET
#all			public--TMPLT			ens1,ens2,ens3 	  10.10.16.0/24,ipset:ipset4all_public	empty			empty (example)
#10.3.2.2		public--TMPLT			empty		  10.10.15.0/24,ipset:ipset4public	fw_ports_set4public	rich_rules_set4public (example)
#10.1.2.3,10.1.2.4	zone1--TMPLT			eth0,eth1,ens01	  10.10.11.0/24,ipset:ipset4zone1	fw_ports_set4zone1	rich_rules_set4zone1 (example)
